<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 2em;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .cache-info {
            background: #f0f8ff;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 1em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .timestamp {
            color: #666;
            font-size: 0.9em;
        }
        .random-id {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #0066cc;
        }
    </style>
    <meta http-equiv="Cache-Control" content="no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate">
    <meta http-equiv="Pragma" content="no-cache">
    <meta http-equiv="Expires" content="0">
</head>
<body>
    <h1><%= title %></h1>

    <div class="cache-info">
        <h2>Cache Headers</h2>
        <p>This page has cache-control headers set to prevent caching:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, proxy-revalidate</code></li>
            <li><code>Pragma: no-cache</code></li>
            <li><code>Expires: 0</code></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cache-info">
        <h2>Dynamic Content</h2>
        <p class="timestamp">Generated at: <%= timestamp %></p>
        <p>Random ID: <span class="random-id"><%= randomId %></span></p>
        <p>This content should be different on each request due to no-cache headers.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cache-info">
        <h2>Testing Notes</h2>
        <p>Use this page to test that Printeer respects no-cache headers and doesn't cache responses that shouldn't be cached.</p>
        <p>Each request should generate a new timestamp and random ID.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>